Kenya recorded just one new Covid-19 death on Sunday, alongside 366 new infections, raising the total number of declared cases since the first one in March to 91,892.
Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi Kagwe said the new death toll was 1,587.
The 366 cases were found following analysis of 4,205 samples in the past 24 hours, raising the total number of samples tested in Kenya so far to 971,522.



